cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on analyzing packet traces and improving network algorithms based on traffic patterns. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a likely category as understanding the structure of packet traces can have implications for network security. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as one of the real-world traces studied is from Facebook. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper proposes a methodology to quantify the complexity of packet traces. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper uses entropy as a measure of complexity and proposes a traffic generator model based on information theory principles.
